description:
Are you looking for spiritual growth and guidance? In this episode of ANN Profiles, Alyssa Truman interviews Joe Reeves, the assistant director of the Sabbath School Personal Ministries Department at the General Conference, about his life and experiences. 

From the Inverse Sabbath School Lesson to growing up in an independent Adventist church, Joe shares his insights on humility, redirection, and the importance of being a part of a church community. 

Join us for an inspiring conversation on spiritual growth and openness to learning.

The Seventh-day Adventist Church has been an established denomination since 1863. It is a global Christian family with over 21 million members who hold the Bible as the ultimate authority. We are believers who promise to help people understand the Bible to find freedom, healing, and hope in Jesus.

Want to learn more about the Seventh-day Adventist Church?
